rComments: Professor Dunning seemed nice and was accessible when you needed her. However, I sat through a 3 hour lecture every week and it was so dry and boring. Getting through each class was difficult without being distracted by something else. Also, readings were heavy each week.

Susan is a very sweet Prof. She clearly cares about your success. However, the lectures can be drier than the Saharan desert. This class was 3 hours long on a Tuesday night. Some weeks were torturous to get through. The class is based on the primary and secondary source readings and how to understand them so readings are essential.

rComments: This prof is the sweetest prof you'll ever meet with the softest voice. For this course, it's mandatory that you come to class as it's basically working through translations of assigned readings. You should be prepared to translate lots of poetry and have solid foundation of Latin grammar and vocab. Otherwise, Prof. Dunning basically walks with you

Susan is a great prof! Her lectures could tend to be boring at times but she is clear on what she expects you to know for the midterms and exams. So you must show up to class.
